fix: add depth_km, lat, lon to briefing for factual assessments

The model's briefing was missing location and depth data, forcing it to either
omit severity-relevant facts or invent them. Now the brief includes these fields
so assessments can reference them factually per soul.md rules ('only state facts
present in tool results'). This enables the model to write location-aware depth
and coordinate references verified against tool data rather than fabricated.

All checkers pass; token budget increased slightly due to additional context.

